onedcx:simpleDc.dcterms:title: Processes Controlling Spatial Snow Distribution Variability at the Macro-Scale Level in Cold Regions

onedcx:dcTerms.dcterms:abstract: Spatial snow distribution is a result of interactions between snow flakes and other factors such as vegetation, wind, and topography.
